main event: A radar-visual UFO sighting was reported at Fort Meade, Maryland, on 15 February 1961.
interesting points: The object exhibited erratic course behavior while being tracked by radar., The object was estimated to be at an altitude of approximately 200 feet and traveling at around 2,000 mph., The preliminary analysis suggested the possibility of the radar target being caused by a temperature inversion., This sighting was part of Project Blue Book, which investigated UFO reports., No interception action was taken during the sighting.
sighted object: an unidentified flying object tracked by radar
witness description: Paul Foster, 2/Lt, and Shelby Adams, 2/Lt, both reliable Master Duty Officers at the 35th Arty Bn
